The paper focuses on deep neural networks (DNNs) and their generalization ability, specifically in the context of adversarial examples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed method involves a learning-based regularization, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the vulnerability of DNNs to adversarial attacks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR).
